Watch van Rooijen spring into action to stop the unknown man from hurting himself. Video: Supplied


Defeated and out of breath the man “curled up in my arms like a baby”, said Van Rooijen.

The man was cuffed by mall security and was whimpering and crying until paramedics arrived.

Netcare911 spokesman Shawn Herbst said the man was transported to hospital in a stable condition.

While police confirmed the incident, spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala said no case was open for investigation as it was an attempt on his own life.

Galleria’s marketing manager Anusha Timul said the shop was able to continue with business soon afterwards.
Attempts to get the man to calm down proved futile. 
Screengrab from video shared on Facebook. 


She denied social media posts claiming that the man had attempted to take his own life after being cornered in a botched robbery.

“He did not threaten or interfere with any staff member or the public. The incident was brought under control quickly and the guy was contained until the ambulance arrived,” said Timul.

Van Rooijen also received medical attention after realising his hand was cut in the struggle for the knife.

“All I know is, that guy was not going to die in front of me,” he said.
The Mercury